Admiralty Head Light.label: Admiralty Head Light
Admiralty Head Light.description: The Admiralty Head Light is a lighthouse located in Fort Casey State Park near Coupeville on Whidbey Island, Washington. Wikipedia

Bressay Lighthouse.label: Bressay Lighthouse
Bressay Lighthouse.description: Bressay Lighthouse is a lighthouse in the Shetland Islands, Scotland, 4 kilometres south-east of Lerwick. It is located on the island of Bressay at Kirkabister Ness overlooking Bressay Sound. Wikipedia

Eddystone Lighthouse.label: Eddystone Lighthouse
Eddystone Lighthouse.description: The Eddystone Lighthouse is on the dangerous Eddystone Rocks, 9 statute miles south of Rame Head, United Kingdom. While Rame Head is in Cornwall, the rocks are in Devon and composed of Precambrian gneiss. Wikipedia

Stroma, Scotland.label: Stroma, Scotland
Stroma, Scotland.description: Stroma is an island off the northern coast of the Scottish mainland. It is the most southerly of the islands in the Pentland Firth between the Orkney Islands and Caithness. Wikipedia

Bull Point Lighthouse.label: Bull Point Lighthouse
Bull Point Lighthouse.description: Bull Point Lighthouse is a lighthouse on Bull Point, about one mile north of the village of Mortehoe, on the northern coast of Devon, England. Wikipedia

Nash Island Light.label: Nash Island Light
Nash Island Light.description: Nash Island Light is a lighthouse on Nash Island at the entrance to Pleasant Bay in Maine. Wikipedia

Sandy Neck Light.label: Sandy Neck Light
Sandy Neck Light.description: Sandy Neck Light was first established in 1826. The current tower was built in 1857 and strengthened in the 1880s. It was discontinued in 1931, replaced by a skeleton tower, which was discontinued in 1952. Wikipedia

Capo dell'Armi Lighthouse.label: Capo dell'Armi Lighthouse
Capo dell'Armi Lighthouse.description: Capo dell'Armi Lighthouse is a lighthouse in Reggio Calabria, southern Italy. Located along the cliffs of the headland, in the comune of Motta San Giovanni it is an important reference for ships coming into the Strait of Sicily from the south. Wikipedia

Vieste Lighthouse.label: Vieste Lighthouse
Vieste Lighthouse.description: Vieste Lighthouse is a lighthouse on the rock of Santa Eufemia, located between the rocks of Santa Croce and San Francesco, just opposite the town of Apulia, Italy. Wikipedia

Alnes Lighthouse.label: Alnes Lighthouse
Alnes Lighthouse.description: Alnes lighthouse was established in 1852 to guide fishing boats safely to the harbor of the small fishing community of Alnes on Godøy island on the west coast of Norway. Wikipedia

Avery Rock Light.label: Avery Rock Light
Avery Rock Light.description: Avery Rock Light was a lighthouse in Avery Rock, Machias Bay, Maine, United States. The square tower was built in 1875, and demolished in 1947 after storm damage. Wikipedia

Bishop Rock, Isles of Scilly.label: Bishop Rock
Bishop Rock, Isles of Scilly.description: Bishop Rock is a small rock, known for its lighthouse, at the westernmost tip of the Isles of Scilly in Cornwall. It is listed in the Guinness Book of Records as the world's smallest island with a building on it. Wikipedia

Brandaris.label: Brandaris
Brandaris.description: The Brandaris is a lighthouse on the Dutch Wadden Sea island Terschelling, in Friesland. The first Brandaris was built in 1323, but it was destroyed in 1570. Wikipedia

Caldey Lighthouse.label: Caldey Lighthouse
Caldey Lighthouse.description: Caldey Lighthouse is located on the south end of Caldey Island, three miles off the south Pembrokeshire, Wales coastline, a small island inhabited by a Cistercian monastery. Wikipedia

Cape Beale Light.label: Cape Beale Light
Cape Beale Light.description: Cape Beale Lightstation is a manned lighthouse on Vancouver Island in British Columbia., Canada. Wikipedia

Cape Race.label: Cape Race
Cape Race.description: Cape Race is a point of land located at the southeastern tip of the Avalon Peninsula on the island of Newfoundland, in Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada. Its name is thought to come from the original Portuguese name for this cape, "Raso", or "bare". Wikipedia

Cape St George Lighthouse (Australia).label: Cape St George Lighthouse
Cape St George Lighthouse (Australia).description: Cape St George Lighthouse was a lighthouse that stood near Jervis Bay Village, Jervis Bay Territory, Australia. It was located about 3 kilometres south of the southern entrance to Jervis Bay. Constructed in 1860 it was active until 1889. Wikipedia

Cape Wrath.label: Cape Wrath
Cape Wrath.description: Cape Wrath is a cape in the parish of Durness, in the county of Sutherland, Highlands, in northern Scotland. It is the most north-westerly point in the mainland United Kingdom. Wikipedia

Dyna Lighthouse.label: Dyna Lighthouse
Dyna Lighthouse.description: Dyna Lighthouse is a coastal lighthouse located on a reef south of Bygdøy, in the Oslofjord in the municipality of Oslo, Norway. It was established in 1875, and automated in 1956. Wikipedia

Currituck Beach Light.label: Currituck Beach Light
Currituck Beach Light.description: The Currituck Beach Light is a lighthouse located on the Outer Banks in Corolla, North Carolina. An example of Gothic Revival architecture, the Currituck Beach Light was added to the National Register of Historic Places on October 15, 1973. Wikipedia

Eborac Island Light.label: Eborac Island Light
Eborac Island Light.description: Eborac Island Light is an active lighthouse on Eborac Island, a small rocky island in the Adolphus Channel just off Cape York, the northern tip of Cape York Peninsula, Far North Queensland, Australia. Wikipedia

Eierland Lighthouse.label: Eierland Lighthouse
Eierland Lighthouse.description: The Eierland Lighthouse is a lighthouse on the northernmost tip of the Dutch island of Texel. It is named for the former island Eierland. The lighthouse was designed by Quirinus Harder and construction began on 25 July 1863. Wikipedia

Execution Rocks Light.label: Execution Rocks Light
Execution Rocks Light.description: Execution Rocks Light is a lighthouse in the middle of Long Island Sound on the border between New Rochelle and Sands Point, New York. It stands 55 feet tall, with a white light flashing every 10 seconds. Wikipedia

Falkner Island Light.label: Falkner Island Light
Falkner Island Light.description: Falkner Island Lighthouse is a lighthouse in Connecticut, United States, off Guilford Harbor on Long Island Sound. Wikipedia

Fenwick Island Light.label: Fenwick Island Light
Fenwick Island Light.description: Fenwick Island Lighthouse is a lighthouse in Delaware, United States, on the Delaware/Maryland border. Wikipedia

Fire Island Light.label: Fire Island Light
Fire Island Light.description: The Fire Island Lighthouse is a visible landmark on the Great South Bay, in southern Suffolk County, New York on the western end of Fire Island, a barrier island off the southern coast of Long Island. Wikipedia

Fort Gratiot Light.label: Fort Gratiot Light
Fort Gratiot Light.description: Fort Gratiot Light, the first lighthouse in the state of Michigan, was constructed north of Fort Gratiot in 1829 by Lucius Lyon, who later became one of Michigan's first U.S. Senators. Wikipedia

Hellevik Lighthouse.label: Hellevik Lighthouse
Hellevik Lighthouse.description: Hellevik Lighthouse is a coastal lighthouse in the municipality of Haram in Møre og Romsdal, Norway. It was first established in 1880, and was automated in 1973. The lighthouse was replaced by a smaller automated light in 1988. Wikipedia

Gabo Island.label: Gabo Island
Gabo Island.description: Gabo Island is a 154-hectare island located off the coast of eastern Victoria, Australia, between Mallacoota and Cape Howe on the border with New South Wales. Wikipedia

Holland Harbor Light.label: Holland Harbor Light
Holland Harbor Light.description: The Holland Harbor Light, known as Big Red, is located in Ottawa County, Michigan at the entrance of a channel connecting Lake Michigan with Lake Macatawa, and which gives access to the city of Holland, Michigan. Wikipedia

Hornby Lighthouse.label: Hornby Lighthouse
Hornby Lighthouse.description: Hornby Lighthouse, also known as South Head Lower Light, is an active lighthouse located on the tip of South Head, New South Wales, Australia, a headland to the north of the suburb Watsons Bay. Wikipedia

Kõpu Lighthouse.label: Kõpu Lighthouse
Kõpu Lighthouse.description: Kõpu Lighthouse is one of the best known symbols and tourist sights on the Estonian island of Hiiumaa. It is one of the oldest lighthouses in the world, having been in continuous use since its completion in 1531. Wikipedia

La Jument.label: La Jument
La Jument.description: La Jument is the name of a lighthouse at the Northwestern part of France, Brittany. The lighthouse is built on a rock about 300 metres from the coast of the island of Ushant, which marks the north-westernmost point of metropolitan France. Wikipedia

Landegode Lighthouse.label: Landegode Lighthouse
Landegode Lighthouse.description: Landegode Lighthouse is a coastal lighthouse located in the municipality of Bodø in Nordland county, Norway. Wikipedia

Lange Jaap.label: Lange Jaap
Lange Jaap.description: Lange Jaap, also known as Kijkduin Light or Den Helder Light, is an active lighthouse near fort Kijkduin in Huisduinen, Netherlands. At a height of 182 feet it is one of the tallest "traditional lighthouse" in the world. Wikipedia

Lighthouse of Genoa.label: Lighthouse of Genoa
Lighthouse of Genoa.description: The Lighthouse of Genoa, is the main lighthouse for the city's port. Besides being an important aid to night navigation in the vicinity, the tower serves as a symbol for the City of Genoa, and is one ... Wikipedia

Mumbles Lighthouse.label: Mumbles Lighthouse
Mumbles Lighthouse.description: Mumbles Lighthouse,completed in 1794, is a lighthouse located in Mumbles, near Swansea. The structure, which sits on the outer of two islands off Mumbles Head, is clearly visible from any point along the five mile sweep of Swansea Bay. Wikipedia

North Tower (lighthouse).label: North Tower
North Tower (lighthouse).description: The North Tower is the unofficial name for one of the lighthouses on the Dutch island Schiermonnikoog, one of the Frisian Islands, on the edge of the North Sea; the other is the South Tower. Wikipedia

Navesink Twin Lights.label: Navesink Twin Lights
Navesink Twin Lights.description: The Navesink Twin Lights is a non-operational lighthouse and museum located in Highlands, Monmouth County, New Jersey, United States, overlooking Sandy Hook Bay, the entrance to the New York Harbor and the Atlantic Ocean. Wikipedia

Oak Island Light.label: Oak Island Light
Oak Island Light.description: The Oak Island Lighthouse is next to the United States Coast Guard station on Oak Island in North Carolina and is owned by the Town of Caswell Beach. Wikipedia

Old Head of Kinsale.label: Old Head of Kinsale
Old Head of Kinsale.description: The Old Head of Kinsale, is a headland near Kinsale, County Cork, Ireland. An early lighthouse was established here in the 17th century by Robert Reading. Wikipedia

Old Orchard Shoal Light.label: Old Orchard Shoal Light
Old Orchard Shoal Light.description: Old Orchard Shoal Light was a sparkplug lighthouse in lower New York Bay marking a large shoal area. It was destroyed by Hurricane Sandy on October 29, 2012. Wikipedia

Phare d'Eckmühl.label: Phare d'Eckmühl
Phare d'Eckmühl.description: The Phare d'Eckmühl, also known as Point Penmarc'h Light or Saint-Pierre Light, is an active lighthouse in Penmarc'h, Finistère department, Brittany, France. At a height of 213 feet it is one of the tallest lighthouses in the world. Wikipedia

Plum Island Range Lights.label: Plum Island Range Lights
Plum Island Range Lights.description: The Plum Island Range Lights are a pair of range lights located on Plum Island in Door County, Wisconsin. They were part of the Plum Island United States Life-Saving Station. Wikipedia

Portland Head Light.label: Portland Head Light
Portland Head Light.description: Portland Head Light is a historic lighthouse in Cape Elizabeth, Maine. The light station sits on a head of land at the entrance of the primary shipping channel into Portland Harbor, which is within Casco Bay in the Gulf of Maine. Wikipedia

Presque Isle Light.label: Presque Isle Light
Presque Isle Light.description: The Presque Isle Light is one of three lighthouses on Lake Erie in U.S. state of Pennsylvania. The lighthouse is located on the northern shore of Presque Isle State Park, near Erie. Wikipedia
Address: Presque Isle Pennisula on Lake Erie

Prudence Island Light.label: Prudence Island Light
Prudence Island Light.description: The Prudence Island Lighthouse, more commonly known locally as the Sandy Point Lighthouse, is located on Prudence Island, Rhode Island and is the oldest lighthouse tower in the state. Wikipedia

Robertson Point Light.label: Robertson Point Light
Robertson Point Light.description: Robertson Point Light, also known as Cremorne Point Light, is an active lighthouse in Cremorne Point, a suburb on the lower North Shore of Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. It is the sibling of Bradleys Head Light. Wikipedia

Sabine Pass Light.label: Sabine Pass Light
Sabine Pass Light.description: The Sabine Pass Light, or Sabine Pass Lighthouse, is a historic lighthouse on the Louisiana side of the Sabine River across from the community of Sabine Pass, Texas in Cameron Parish, Louisiana. Wikipedia

Sandy Hook Light.label: Sandy Hook Lighthouse
Sandy Hook Light.description: The Sandy Hook Lighthouse, located about one and a half statute miles inland from the tip of Sandy Hook, New Jersey, is the oldest working lighthouse in the United States. It was designed and built in 1764 by Isaac Conro. Wikipedia

Santa Barbara Light.label: Santa Barbara Light
Santa Barbara Light.description: Santa Barbara Lighthouse was a lighthouse in California, United States, on the Santa Barbara Harbour, California. Wikipedia

Skokholm Lighthouse.label: Skokholm Lighthouse
Skokholm Lighthouse.description: Skokholm Lighthouse is a lighthouse found on the small Welsh island of Skokholm, just off the south-west coast of Pembrokeshire. Wikipedia

Split Rock Lighthouse.label: Split Rock Lighthouse
Split Rock Lighthouse.description: Split Rock Lighthouse is a lighthouse located southwest of Silver Bay, Minnesota, USA on the North Shore of Lake Superior. Wikipedia

St. Catherine's Oratory.label: St. Catherine's Oratory
St. Catherine's Oratory.description: St. Catherine's Oratory is a medieval lighthouse on St. Catherine's Down near the southern coast of the Isle of Wight, the Back of the Wight. Wikipedia

Stonington Harbor Light.label: Stonington Harbor Light
Stonington Harbor Light.description: The Stonington Harbor Light is a historic nineteenth century lighthouse located on the east side of Stonington Harbor in Stonington, Connecticut. Wikipedia

Strumble Head Lighthouse.label: Strumble Head Lighthouse
Strumble Head Lighthouse.description: Strumble Head Lighthouse stands on Ynys Meicel, a rocky island at the northwest corner of Pencaer, five miles west of the town of Fishguard, in northern Pembrokeshire, Wales. Wikipedia

Westerlichttoren.label: Westerlichttoren
Westerlichttoren.description: The Westerlichttoren or West Schouwen is a lighthouse in Haamstede, Netherlands. Designed by L. Valk, it was built in 1837. At 53 m above ground and a light stand at 58 m above sea level it is one of the tallest lighthouses in the Netherlands. Wikipedia

Beachy Head.label: Beachy Head
Beachy Head.description: Beachy Head is a chalk headland in Southern England, close to the town of Eastbourne in the county of East Sussex, immediately east of the Seven Sisters. Wikipedia

Cape Schanck Lighthouse.label: Cape Schanck Lighthouse
Cape Schanck Lighthouse.description: The Cape Schanck lighthouse was built in 1859 as the second coastal lighthouse in Victoria. It is located on the southernmost tip of the Mornington Peninsula in Victoria, Australia. The tower was built from limestone, it is 21 metres tall. Wikipedia

Mahukona, Hawaii.label: Mahukona, Hawaii
Mahukona, Hawaii.description: Māhukona is a former settlement on the island of Hawaiʻi. The extinct submerged volcano Māhukona, off shore and to the south, is named for this area. It was once the terminus of the Hawaiian Railroad. Wikipedia

Naze.label: Naze
Naze.description: The Naze is a headland on the east coast of England. It is on the coast of Essex just north of Blackwater and projects into the North Sea. Wikipedia

Point Lonsdale Lighthouse.label: Point Lonsdale Lighthouse
Point Lonsdale Lighthouse.description: Point Lonsdale Lighthouse, also known as the Point Lonsdale Signal Station, is close to the township of Point Lonsdale in the Borough of Queenscliffe, Victoria, Australia. Wikipedia

Salt Island, Anglesey.label: Salt Island, Anglesey
Salt Island, Anglesey.description: Salt Island is an island joined to Holy Island, itself an island joined to Anglesey in North Wales. It is a natural provider of shelter for the towns Old Harbour from the Irish Sea and is also part of ... Wikipedia

South Stack.label: South Stack
South Stack.description: South Stack is an island situated just off Holy Island on the northwest coast of Anglesey. It is famous as the location of one of Wales' most spectacular South Stack Lighthouse. It has a height of 41 metres. Wikipedia

Trwyn Du Lighthouse.label: Trwyn Du Lighthouse
Trwyn Du Lighthouse.description: Trwyn Du Lighthouse is a lighthouse between Dinmor Point near Penmon and Ynys Seriol, or Puffin Island, south east Anglesey, at the north entrance to the Menai Strait and marking the passage between the two islands. Wikipedia

Absecon Light.label: Absecon Light
Absecon Light.description: The Absecon Light is a coastal lighthouse located in the north end of Atlantic City, New Jersey, overlooking Absecon Inlet. Wikipedia

Amelia Island Light.label: Amelia Island Light
Amelia Island Light.description: The Amelia Island Light is the oldest existing lighthouse in the state of Florida in the United States. It is located near the northern end of Amelia Island in the northeastern part of the state. Wikipedia

Avery Point Light.label: Avery Point Light
Avery Point Light.description: Avery Point Lighthouse is a lighthouse in Groton, Connecticut, United States, on the Avery Point Campus of the University of Connecticut. Wikipedia

Barrenjoey, New South Wales.label: Barrenjoey, New South Wales
Barrenjoey, New South Wales.description: Barrenjoey is a locality in the suburb of Palm Beach, at the most northern tip of Pittwater. The headland is mostly made up of Hawkesbury sandstone which overlays Narrabeen shale. Wikipedia

Bathurst Lighthouse.label: Bathurst Lighthouse
Bathurst Lighthouse.description: Bathurst Lighthouse is one of two lighthouses on Rottnest Island, the other being Wadjemup Lighthouse. It is located on Bathurst Point, in the north east of the island, and was activated in 1900. Wikipedia

Borkum Großer Light.label: Borkum Großer Light
Borkum Großer Light.description: Borkum Großer Light, also known as Borkum Neuer Light, is an active lighthouse on the island of Borkum, Leer district, state of Lower Saxony, Germany. Wikipedia

Cape Meares Light.label: Cape Meares Light
Cape Meares Light.description: The Cape Meares Light is an inactive lighthouse on the coast of Oregon. It is located on Cape Meares just south of Tillamook Bay. It is open to the public. Wikipedia

Cape Fear Light.label: Cape Fear Light
Cape Fear Light.description: Cape Fear Lighthouse was built in 1903, replacing the Bald Head Lighthouse as the main navigation aid for Cape Fear and the Frying Pan Shoals off the coast of the U.S. state of North Carolina. It stood near the cape on Bald Head Island. Wikipedia

Cape Mendocino Light.label: Cape Mendocino Light
Cape Mendocino Light.description: Cape Mendocino Light was a navigation light at Cape Mendocino, California. The former lighthouse was relocated to Shelter Cove near Point Delgada, California in 1998, and the historic Fresnel lens to Ferndale, California in 1948. Wikipedia

Cape Poge Light.label: Cape Poge Light
Cape Poge Light.description:
Cape Poge Light, sometimes called Cape Pogue Light, is at the northeast tip of Chappaquiddick Island that is part of Martha's Vineyard, off the coast of Cape Cod, Massachusetts.
At least four towers have been built on Cape Poge, with many moves. Wikipedia

Chicken Rock.label: Chicken Rock
Chicken Rock.description: Chicken Rock is the southernmost island administered by the Isle of Man and belongs to the parish of Rushen. It lies to the southwest of the Calf of Man, 4.5 kilometres off Spanish Head on the Manx mainland. Wikipedia

Crabtree Ledge Light.label: Crabtree Ledge Light
Crabtree Ledge Light.description: Crabtree Ledge Light was a sparkplug lighthouse on Frenchman Bay, Maine. It was first established in 1890 and deactivated in 1933. Wikipedia

Crooked River Light.label: Crooked River Lighthouse
Crooked River Light.description: The Crooked River Light, also known as the Carrabelle Light, was built in 1895 to replace the Dog Island Light on Dog Island, which had been destroyed in 1875 by a hurricane. Wikipedia

Dagebüll lighthouse.label: Dagebüll lighthouse
Dagebüll lighthouse.description: Dagebüll lighthouse is a retired lighthouse in Dagebüll, Nordfriesland, Germany. Until its replacement in 1988 by a direction light on the dock of the Dagebüll ferry port, it served as the lower light of the Dagebüll range of leading lights. Wikipedia

Desdemona Sands Light.label: Desdemona Sands Light
Desdemona Sands Light.description:
Desdemona Sands Light was a lighthouse located on the Pacific coast of the U.S. state of Oregon, at the mouth of the Columbia River to aid navigation of the Columbia Bar.
It was built in 1901 or 1902 as a replacement for Point Adams Light. Wikipedia

Eagle Island, County Mayo.label: Eagle Island, County Mayo
Eagle Island, County Mayo.description: Eagle Island is a small island at the north end of the Mullet Peninsula in Erris off the north west County Mayo Atlantic Ocean coast in Ireland. There is a lighthouse on the island. Wikipedia

Erie Harbor North Pier Light.label: Erie Harbor North Pier Light
Erie Harbor North Pier Light.description: The Erie Harbor North Pier Light, also known as the Presque Isle North Pier Light, is one of the three lighthouses near Erie, Pennsylvania in the United States. Wikipedia

Fort Point Light, San Francisco.label: Fort Point Light
Fort Point Light, San Francisco.description: Fort Point Light was a lighthouse on Fort Point, directly beneath the south anchorage of the Golden Gate Bridge in San Francisco, California. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1970, reference #70000146. Wikipedia

Great Captain Island Light.label: Great Captain Island Light
Great Captain Island Light.description: Great Captain Island Lighthouse is a lighthouse on Great Captain Island in the western Long Island Sound off the coast of Greenwich, Connecticut, United States. The lighthouse is no longer in use. Wikipedia

Haifa Lee Breakwater Light.label: Haifa Lee Breakwater Light
Haifa Lee Breakwater Light.description:
Haifa Lee Breakwater Light is a lighthouse in Haifa, Israel. It is located at the end of the quay serving as the inner breakwater of the Port of Haifa.
Until 2007 the light was located on top of a 31 feet white square concrete harbor control tower. Wikipedia

Haig Point Range Lights.label: Haig Point Range Lights
Haig Point Range Lights.description: The Haig Point Range Lights were range lights on Calibogue Sound at the northeastern end of Daufuskie Island in Beaufort County, South Carolina. Wikipedia

Heligoland lighthouse.label: Heligoland lighthouse
Heligoland lighthouse.description: Heligoland lighthouse is located on Germany's only offshore island, Heligoland. Constructed during World War II as an anti-aircraft tower, it was turned into a lighthouse in 1952. Wikipedia

Hook Lighthouse.label: Hook Lighthouse
Hook Lighthouse.description: The Hook Lighthouse is a building situated at the tip of the Hook Peninsula in County Wexford, in Ireland. It is the oldest working lighthouse in the world after the Tower of Hercules in La Coruña. Wikipedia

Horsburgh Lighthouse.label: Horsburgh Lighthouse
Horsburgh Lighthouse.description: Horsburgh Lighthouse is a lighthouse which marks the eastern entrance to the Straits of Singapore. It is situated on Pedra Branca island. Wikipedia

Cape Sorell.label: Cape Sorell
Cape Sorell.description: Cape Sorell is the headland and lighthouse outside Macquarie Harbour on the West Coast of Tasmania. It is an important orientation point for all vessels entering Macquarie Heads - and then through Hells Gates at the entrance to the harbour. Wikipedia

Cape Byron Light.label: Cape Byron Light
Cape Byron Light.description: Cape Byron Light is an active lighthouse located at Cape Byron, New South Wales, Australia. The cape is the easternmost point of the mainland of Australia, located about 3 kilometres northeast of the town of Byron Bay. Wikipedia
